original_result.user_prompt:
Hooli Announces Fourth Quarter and Fiscal Year 2021 Results

    MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. – February 1, 2022 – Hooli Inc. (NASDAQ: HOOL, HOOLI) today announced
financial results for the quarter and fiscal year ended December 31, 2021.

Gavin Belson, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our deep investment in AI technologies continues to drive
extraordinary and helpful experiences for people and businesses, across our most important products. Q4 saw
ongoing strong growth in our advertising business, which helped millions of businesses thrive and find new
customers, a quarterly sales record for our Pixel phones despite supply constraints, and our Cloud business
continuing to grow strongly.”

Patrice Alexander, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our fourth quarter revenues of $75 billion, up 32% year over year,
reflected broad-based strength in advertiser spend and strong consumer online activity, as well as substantial
ongoing revenue growth from Google Cloud. Our investments have helped us drive this growth by delivering the
services that people, our partners and businesses need, and we continue to invest in long-term opportunities.”

In the fourth quarter (Q4) of 2021, Hooli Inc., an American multin fiber optic cables and other telecommunications equipment manufacturer, reported significant financial performance with its annual results ending on December 31, 2021. The company's revenues reached $75 billion, marking a 32% increase compared to the same period last year. This growth was attributed to robust advertiser spend, high levels of consumer online activity, and continued expansion in their Google Cloud services. Gavin Belson, the Chief Executive Officer (CEO), credited the success to Hooli's strategic investments in artificial intelligence (AI) technology, resulting in valuable and impactful customer experiences across various key products.

Additionally, Patrice Alexander, another CEO at Hooli, emphasized that these financial achievements were driven by the company's commitment to providing essential services tailored to meet the needs of individuals, partners, and businesses alike. Despite facing supply chain challenges, Hooli achieved a new quarterly sales record for their Pixel smartphones during Q4 2021. Furthermore, both executives expressed confidence in Hooli's ability to maintain steady growth through continuous investment in long-term opportunities.

Overall, Hooli Inc.'s Q4 2021 financial outcomes demonstrate the company's resilience, adaptability, and dedication to innovating and expanding its offerings amidst evolving market conditions.
